To maximize loading speed and keep the website’s initial bundle size tiny, Stripe’s engineering team did not load a heavy 3D library. Instead, they wrote a bespoke, lightweight **raw WebGL wrapper** with custom **GLSL Shaders** running directly on the GPU.

